<!-- Show this bit first -->

<h1>What kind of content do you need a form for?</h1>
<ul class="wh-content-type-selector">
  <li>
    <h5><span class="icon icon-clock-o"></span> Time-based publishing</h5>
    <p>
      Publishable content starts as a draft, then goes
      live at a specific time you define. Articles, galleries, and podcasts
      are all examples of time-based publishing.
    </p>
    {{#link-to 'wh.content.start' class="btn btn-neutral icon icon-plus-sign"}} Create publishable{{/link-to}}
  </li>
  <li>
    <h5><span class="icon icon-files-o"></span> Objects in a set</h5>
    <p>
      You need to create a bunch of pages based upon content you
      add into a repeatable form. A collection of comic books
      are an example of objects in a set.
    </p>
    {{#link-to 'wh.content.start' class="btn btn-neutral icon icon-plus-sign"}} Create new set{{/link-to}}
  </li>
  <li>
    <h5><span class="icon icon-file-o"></span> One-off</h5>
    <p>
      One-offs are for single pages or content. You simply
      need a form to edit the content of just one thing.
      An about us page or a changable widget is an example of a one-off.
    </p>
    {{#link-to 'wh.content.start' class="btn btn-neutral icon icon-plus-sign"}} Create a one-off{{/link-to}}
  </li>
</ul>

<!-- Then, after they select one of the above, show this bit -->

<form class="wy-form-stacked" {{action createType on="submit"}}>
  <div class="wh-content-type-create-form">
    <h5>What is the name of your new set?</h5>
    <div class="wy-control-group">
      <div class="wy-control">
        <div class="wy-inline-validate wy-inline-validate-info">
          {{input value=newTypeName placeholder="ex: comics" class="wy-input-large"}}
            <span class="wy-input-context"> Use a short lowercase word, without spaces.</span>
          {{#if isDuplicate}}
            <span class="wy-input-context"> There is already an content type with that name</span>
          {{/if}}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wy-button-group">
      <button type="submit" class="btn btn-neutral icon icon-ok-sign"> Let's create a {{#if newTypeName}}{{newTypeName}}{{/if}} form!</button>
      {{#link-to 'wh.content.start' class="btn btn-small btn-link icon icon-remove-sign"}} Cancel{{/link-to}}
    </div>
    <p></p>
  </div>

  <hr/>
  <h5>The URLs will follow this format</h5>
  <ul class="wy-plain-list-disc">
    <li>A list of all <code>{{#if newTypeName}}{{newTypeName}}{{else}}comics{{/if}}</code> will exist at <code>http://www.yoursite.com/{{#if newTypeName}}{{newTypeName}}{{else}}comics{{/if}}</code></li>
    <li>Individual <code>{{#if newTypeName}}{{newTypeName}}{{else}}comics{{/if}}</code> will exist at <code>http://www.yoursite.com/{{#if newTypeName}}{{newTypeName}}{{else}}comics{{/if}}/$name/</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Editable HTML templates will be generated in</h5>

  <ul class="wy-plain-list-disc">
    <li>The list of all <code>{{#if newTypeName}}{{newTypeName}}{{else}}comics{{/if}}</code> template will exist in <code>/templates/{{#if newTypeName}}{{newTypeName}}{{else}}comics{{/if}}/list.swig</code></li>
    <li>The template for a single <code>{{#if newTypeName}}{{newTypeName}}{{else}}comics{{/if}}</code> will exist in <code>/templates/{{#if newTypeName}}{{newTypeName}}{{else}}comics{{/if}}/individual.swig</code></li>
  </ul>
</form>
